      About this item

      • ALL-IN-ONE: Everything you need in a single soundbar with two woofers and tweeters built in, so you can enjoy rich sound that will fill your room
      • DOLBY DIGITAL 5.1 / DTS VIRTUAL:X: Dolby Digital 5.1 capable creates realistic surround sound by projecting it from all around you, while DTS Virtual: X expands your listening experience without having to add extra speakers
      • Q-SYMPHONY: Perfectly synchronized, fully immersive audio floods your room all at once, using every speaker in compatible Samsung TV and soundbars*
      • BUILT-IN CENTER SPEAKER: The built-in center speaker is dedicated to delivering enhanced dialogue, so you won't miss a word, no matter how faint the conversation or how intense the background music or action is
      • ADAPTIVE SOUND LITE: Enjoy dynamically optimized audio with enhanced voice clarity so you can follow along with action-packed games and blockbuster films
      • MUSIC MODE: Experience vocals and instruments in studio-grade clarity, allowing you to hear every note as the artists intended
      • BLUETOOTH MULTI CONNECTION: Connect two smart devices at the same time so you can conveniently switch and play songs from different devices**

      Product Description

      The all-in-one S50B premium soundbar delivers sharp and rich audio. Experience captivating 3D audio with Dolby Digital 5.1 capable and DTS Virtual:X. Perfectly synchronized TV and soundbar sound brings a new level of immersion to your favorite content. Don't miss a word with crisp and clear dialogue thanks to a built-in center speaker. With Tap Sound, you can play your music or podcasts from your mobile device to your soundbar with a simple tap***

      *Q-Symphony is compatible with select 20210 - 2022 Samsung TVs. Please refer to samsung.com for more information. Soundbar must be connected to TV via HDMI to enable Q-Symphony function. **Soundbar mobile connection is not available when connected to the TV. Requires Bluetooth® compatible devices. ***Tap sound is only compatible with select Samsung mobile devices, with Android 8.1 and above. Tap Sound requires SmartThings app to activate
      and set up. This service only works when Soundbar and mobile are on.

      How customer reviews and ratings work

      Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

      To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

      5 out of 5 stars
      Great little sound bar.
      I got this sound bar to go with the Samsung TV my fiance got me for my birthday a couple of months ago. I figured it was the best way to go since the TV is Q-Symphony compatible as well. Let's just say so far so good. Now I can sit back in my starter man cave and watch a few animes or catch the game and not just rely on the TV speakers. So if you are a Samsung Knight like myself, being able use my phone to customize settings made it a plus for me. So this sound bar gets 5 stars from me just because it serves its purpose and sounds good in my space.

      • J. Webber
        5.0 out of 5 stars Blows Vizio out of the water.
        Reviewed in the United States on February 21, 2025
        Style: HW-S60DPattern: SoundbarVerified Purchase
        I grabbed this on sale at 250 hoping it would be better than my previous soundbars. I had an Insiginia that was too tinny, and old, so it made sense... and I have been rocking 2 Vizio M Series bars, 2 different models, on 2 different eARC Dolby Atmos setups. When I upgraded to an OLED recently I noticed that both of the Vizio Soundbars had a terrible issue of cutting out low bass frequencies when at low volumes and it started to drive me absolutely nuts. There is nothing physically or functionally wrong with either of the Vizio bars, it's just how they are - and that's a huge problem. They were also both 2.1 speakers.

        Now this Samsung blows every soundbar I've heard out of the water. Got it out of the box today, setup was easy enough, remote functions well and the instructions made it easy to figure out... this thing has the perfect thumping bass I was looking for. Not quiet, you can feel it in your chest a bit, but it isn't blowing the room apart or muddying the other sounds and tones. The extra speakers compared to what I had are surely helping, but it also has great quality for my games, PS5, Switch, All of my retro systems running through a Retrotink 4K, from NES to PS3 era... it all sounds great and works well with this bar. And no more annoying poppy crackling, in and out low frequency bass at low volumes - and trust me I checked with my ear right on the thing at the lowest possible volumes. It sounds great!

        The best tip I can give, be sure to find the best "base" setting you like first, for me it was Game mode, then adjust your bass and sub levels with the remote, then treble, and THEN, do your channel level. I'd suggest focusing on the center first then boost or lower your side speakers.

        It sounds great. I'm very happy. Paired right away no issues at all with the LG B4 OLED 48".

        If you're like me and already have a bunch of stuff plugged up and want an all in one soundbar with no separate subwoofer or speakers for a bedroom-sized setup, look no further. You've found one of the best, especially for the price. Even came with the mounting bits - but you WILL need to provide 2 of your own screws and possibly drywall anchors to put the mount hinges up, those are not included!

      • R. Mcdonald
        5.0 out of 5 stars Really Good Sound
        Reviewed in the United States on April 16, 2024
        Style: HW-S60BPattern: SoundbarVerified Purchase
        I must say first off, I bought this for my projector and tv and was not really impressed with the sound especially the voice enhancement feature or the bass. I used the small manual they send with it, and it really doesn't tell you much about the soundbar just basically how to set it up and what the buttons do but no info other than that and I was very discouraged and then I downloaded the online full manual and man what a difference that made.
        The online manual shows you what all and how to make more adjustments than you can imagine and after I did them it sounds like a totally different soundbar.
        For you that don't know it has a small equalizer, but it only works in standard mode, and it really increases voice enhancements and overall sound in standard mode.
        This Samsung HW-S60B sound bar is much better than the Bose TV Soundbar I had before I purchased this one and never was satisfied with the sound of the unit and it had very few adjustments and voice enhancements wasn't that good to me and then it just stopped working 27 days after purchase, so I returned it and very glad it did because this one is much better to me. I have always loved Boss products but seems like they have really cut back on what got them to where they are, Quality.
        Not sure about the low reviews but just maybe some have not downloaded the full manual and don't realize all the different adjustments that you can make to your liking on this bar.
        You will not get the thumping bass out of this soundbar as you will not out of any especially in this price range without adding a subwoofer, but the bass is really good much better that a tv for a small soundbar, and the volume is rated at 120 watts and is very clear no matter how loud you play it.
        The remote works very good and feels of quality as any Samsung product I have from them. It also has control buttons on the unit if the remote goes out for some reason, the Boss didn't have any other way to control it.
        Yes, I am much happier with this Samsung soundbar, it really surprised me, but I don't know why because Samsung has really become a leader in innovation and quality.
        Now I must tell you the only subwoofer it will connect to is a Samsung subwoofer SWA-W510 per Bluetooth and it is small and around $300.00. But I also have a sound system with a subwoofer and this bar pairs very well with my system making a huge difference in its all around sound.
